dptrain: is the file used to the training. Is written according to DeepMD documentation (https://docs.deepmodeling.com/projects/deepmd/en/stable/model/index.html)

job_deepmd_compress_cpu_vives.sh: used to launch compress phase within any step

job_deepmd_dptest_cpu_vives.sh: launches the test phase (optional)

job_deepmd_freeze_cpu_vives.sh: handles the freezing within any step

job_deepmd_train_gpu_vives.sh: launches the training during the training phase

properties.txt: contains the atom type and the associations of each atom type to a number in order to keep track of the indexes 
associated to atoms. Moreover it stores the masses of each atom


